 future planning</span></p>", "<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">None.</span>"], "授業外学習2": "<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Students will work outside of class equal to the time in class over the semester. This means for this class expect to spend at least 60-90 minutes a week doing class preparation, studying for tests, and other general preparation. For any particular week this time may be more or less depending on the week in the semester. Please consult the class by class outline below.</span></span></span></span></span></span>"}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["TOEIC SKILLS 2 New \nAbax \nISBN 978178547820"], "教科書/Required texts1": ["Graham-Marr", "TOEIC SKILLS 2 New", "Abax", "2021 年", "9781785470820", ""], "参考文献・資料/Reference books0": ["None"], "学位授与の方針との関連Relationship to Diploma Policy0": ["Each subject is placed on the curriculum based on the Diploma Policy (DP) and Curriculum Policy (CP) established by each faculty and graduate school. \nBy studying these subjects with the DP and CP in mind, you will develop the abilities expected by each faculty and graduate school. \nThe DP, CP and curriculum charts (list of subjects, etc.) for each faculty and graduate school are posted in the link below, so please use this as reference for your study plan. \nhttps://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1 \n*This is a link to kwic (only current students can view this)"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "60% Unit Tests (3x20), 20% Homework and Preparation 20%, Participation"], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note There are no make-up tests or assignments. Unexcused absences on test days will result in a score of zero. If the absence is excused due to medicinal reasons or other, the student will receive the class average score for the quiz/assignment.Plagiarism means copying other peoples' language and claiming it as your own. This also includes automatic and machine translation, as well as AI language generation. Any instances of plagiarism will result in a score of zero for the task, and possibly for the entire course.Late submissions of tasks will be penalised in the following way:Less than 7 days late, or in the following lesson= -50%More than 7 days late= -100%Absences strictly follow KGU policy. Three absences is an automatic failure.&nbsp;出席、遅刻の制度については以下URL先をご確認ください。/ Please refer to the following URL for details regarding the attendance and tardiness policy.　https://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/area/detail?areaId=7144&amp;directLink=1"], "備考Note0": ["To take this class, you must apply for level certification in advance. For details, please check the \"Course Registration Procedures\" at the URL below (KWIC Cabinet)."], "備考Note1": ["英語インテンシブ・プログラム　履修について"], "備考Note2": ["2026年01月20日 10時54分05秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "春学期／Spring", "月曜４時限／Monday 4", "春学期／Spring", "４別－２０５"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【250】Skills-based English(TOEIC)　１／Skills-based English(TOEIC)", "管理部署": 20, "単位数": 1, "担当者": "マクナマラ　Ｓ．（MCNAMARA STEPHEN） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "申込制", "開講期": 1, "時限1": 3, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\nThere are no make-up tests or assignments. Unexcused absences on test days will result in a score of zero. If the absence is excused due to medicinal reasons or other, the student will receive the class average score for the quiz/assignment.\nPlagiarism means copying other peoples' language and claiming it as your own. This also includes automatic and machine translation, as well as AI language generation. Any instances of plagiarism will result in a score of zero for the task, and possibly for the entire course.\nLate submissions of tasks will be penalised in the following way:\nLess than 7 days late, or in the following lesson= -50%\nMore than 7 days late= -100%\nAbsences strictly follow KGU policy. Three absences is an automatic failure. \n出席、遅刻の制度については以下URL先をご確認ください。/ Please refer to the following URL for details regarding the attendance and tardiness policy.\nhttps://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/area/detail?areaId=7144&directLink=1"}